organization_id: The GLOBE ID assigned to the school or organization
org_name: The name of the reporting school or other institution
site_id: The GLOBE ID assigned to the site
site_name: The name assigned to the site where the data were collected; the name is selected by the reporting person as part of site definition
latitude: The latitude of the site where data were observed in decimal degrees
longitude: The longitude of the site where date were observed in decimal degrees
elevation: The elevation of the site where data were observed in meters
measured_on: The date only of when the data were observed in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC)
air temp dailies:minimum temp (deg C): The minimum air temperature since the previous day's reading in degrees Celsius; note that measurements must be taken within one hour of local solar noon
air temp dailies:maximum temp (deg C): The maximum air temperature since the previous day's reading in degrees Celsius; note that measurements must be taken within one hour of local solar noon
aerosols:observed sky color: Sky color: deep blue, blue, light blue, pale blue, or milky
aerosols:observed sky clarity: Sky clarity: unusually clear, clear, somewhat hazy, very hazy, extremely hazy
aerosols:associated remote sensor: Satellite mission or instrument to which aerosol observation may be compared
aerosols:remote sensor overflight time: Time the associated remote sensor most nearly flies over the aerosol measurement site
aerosols:remote sensor maximum elevation: The highest angle the satellite mission is above the horizon for the location and time of the aerosol measurement
aerosols:aerosol photometer type: The type of instrument (sun photometer) used to measure aerosols
aerosols:aerosol photometer serial numbe: The serial number of the instrument used to measure aerosols
barometric pressures:pressure method: Type of barometer use to measure atmospheric pressure
barometric pressures:pressure: Atmospheric pressure at the measurement site
barometric pressures:sea level pressure: Atmospheric pressure at the measurement site adjusted to the value that would be observed if the sight were at sea level; these values allow pressure comparisons independent of topography.
sky conditions:volcanic ash: Volcanic ash obscured >25% of the sky
sky conditions:heavy rain: Heavy rain obscured >25% of the sky
sky conditions:heavy snow: Heavy snow obscured >25% of the sky
sky conditions:blowing snow: Blowing snow obscured >25% of the sky
sky conditions:is citizen science: Cloud and contrail observations were taken by a public citizen scientist
sky conditions:comments: Comments on cloud and contrail observations
precipitations:days accumulated: The number of days precipitation has accumulated since the previous measurement
precipitations:liquid accumulation: The depth of rain or melted snow
precipitations:ph: The pH of the precipitation (rain or melted snow)
precipitations:ph method: The method used to measure pH: paper, pen, or meter
precipitations:vis total liquid equivale: The depth of melted new snow
land covers:muc code: MUC code of the land cover site
land covers:muc description: Description of the land cover site MUC code
